.space-y-8
  %section
    %p.text-sm.font-semibold.uppercase.tracking-wide.text-sky-700.dark:text-sky-300 Random Record
    %h1.mt-2.text-3xl.font-bold Organization Detail
    %p.mt-3.max-w-3xl.text-gray-700.dark:text-gray-300
      Discovery uses IAM_SYSTEM because this page intentionally hacks around normal authorization to find IDs the caller does not already know. After it discovers a real admin user, ordinary non-MSP detail expansion uses that admin identity.

  %section.rounded.border.border-amber-300.bg-amber-50.p-4.text-amber-950.dark:border-amber-700.dark:bg-amber-950.dark:text-amber-100
    %h2.text-lg.font-semibold Demo-Only Auth Hacking
    %p.mt-2.text-sm
      This random explorer is not a production feature. It enumerates organization IDs, account IDs, MSP relationships, and admin user IDs specifically so the demo can jump into interesting records during a live seed. A real caller should not be able to discover those identifiers unless they already know them or are already authorized in that context.
    %p.mt-2.text-sm
      The page switches to the discovered admin after bootstrap. Private MSP relationship checks remain IAM_SYSTEM-only because the MSP mapping is intentionally invisible to ordinary callers.

  - if @error
    %section.rounded.border.border-red-200.bg-red-50.p-4.text-red-900.dark:border-red-800.dark:bg-red-950.dark:text-red-100
      %h2.font-semibold No Admin-Visible Organization Found
      %p.mt-2= @error
      - if @attempts.present?
        %table.mt-4.w-full.text-left.text-sm
          %thead
            %tr
              %th.py-1 Organization
              %th.py-1 Random Account
              %th.py-1 Admin User
              %th.py-1 MSP
          %tbody
            - @attempts.each do |attempt|
              %tr.border-t.border-red-200.dark:border-red-800
                %td.py-1.font-mono.text-xs= attempt[:organization_id]
                %td.py-1.font-mono.text-xs= attempt[:account_id]
                %td.py-1.font-mono.text-xs= attempt[:admin_user_id] || 'none'
                %td.py-1= attempt[:msp_managed] ? 'yes' : 'no'
      %p.mt-4
        %a.font-medium.text-sky-700.hover:underline.dark:text-sky-300{ href: random_record_path } Try another random record
  - else
    %section.grid.gap-4.md:grid-cols-4
      .rounded.border.border-gray-200.p-4.dark:border-gray-700
        %span.block.text-sm.text-gray-600.dark:text-gray-300 Organization
        %span.mt-1.block.break-all.font-mono.text-xs= @organization.id
        %span.mt-2.block.font-semibold= @organization.name
      .rounded.border.border-gray-200.p-4.dark:border-gray-700
        %span.block.text-sm.text-gray-600.dark:text-gray-300 Admin User
        %span.mt-1.block.break-all.font-mono.text-xs= @admin_user_id
      .rounded.border.border-gray-200.p-4.dark:border-gray-700
        %span.block.text-sm.text-gray-600.dark:text-gray-300 Accounts
        %span.mt-1.block.text-2xl.font-bold= @account_count
      .rounded.border.border-gray-200.p-4.dark:border-gray-700
        %span.block.text-sm.text-gray-600.dark:text-gray-300 Users
        %span.mt-1.block.text-2xl.font-bold= @total_user_count

    - if @msp_relationship
      %section.rounded.border.border-amber-300.bg-amber-50.p-4.text-amber-950.dark:border-amber-700.dark:bg-amber-950.dark:text-amber-100
        %h2.text-lg.font-semibold MSP-Managed Account
        %p.mt-2.text-sm
          This selected account is attached to an MSP through the private internal MSP mapping. The mapping is discovered with IAM_SYSTEM because non-system requests are supposed to behave as if the mapping does not exist; they should not be able to learn the MSP account ID, MSP organization ID, or relationship direction unless that knowledge was already available through another authorized path.
        .mt-4.grid.gap-3.md:grid-cols-2
          .rounded.border.border-amber-200.p-3.dark:border-amber-800
            %span.block.text-sm MSP Account
            %span.mt-1.block.break-all.font-mono.text-xs= @msp_relationship.fetch(:msp_account_id)
          .rounded.border.border-amber-200.p-3.dark:border-amber-800
            %span.block.text-sm MSP Organization
            %span.mt-1.block.break-all.font-mono.text-xs= @msp_relationship.fetch(:msp_organization_id)
          .rounded.border.border-amber-200.p-3.dark:border-amber-800
            %span.block.text-sm Reflected Grant Status
            %span.mt-1.block.font-semibold= @msp_reflected_status.fetch(:status)
          .rounded.border.border-amber-200.p-3.dark:border-amber-800
            %span.block.text-sm Reflected Progress
            %span.mt-1.block= "#{@msp_reflected_status.fetch(:loaded_count)} / #{@msp_reflected_status.fetch(:total_count)}"

    %section
      %h2.text-xl.font-semibold Useful Links
      .mt-4.grid.gap-3.md:grid-cols-2
        %a.rounded.border.border-gray-200.p-3.font-medium.transition.hover:border-sky-500.hover:bg-sky-50.dark:border-gray-700.dark:hover:border-sky-400.dark:hover:bg-gray-800{ href: random_record_path } Pick Another Random Record
        %a.rounded.border.border-gray-200.p-3.font-medium.transition.hover:border-sky-500.hover:bg-sky-50.dark:border-gray-700.dark:hover:border-sky-400.dark:hover:bg-gray-800{ href: random_record_detail_path(@organization.id, @selected_account_id) } Refresh This Record
        - unless @msp_relationship
          %a.rounded.border.border-gray-200.p-3.font-medium.transition.hover:border-sky-500.hover:bg-sky-50.dark:border-gray-700.dark:hover:border-sky-400.dark:hover:bg-gray-800{ href: account_view_path(@selected_account_id, as: @admin_user_id) } Open Selected Account Page
        - if @msp_relationship
          %a.rounded.border.border-gray-200.p-3.font-medium.transition.hover:border-sky-500.hover:bg-sky-50.dark:border-gray-700.dark:hover:border-sky-400.dark:hover:bg-gray-800{ href: msp_graphql_query_path(kind: "accounts", msp_account_id: @msp_relationship.fetch(:msp_account_id), admin_user_id: @admin_user_id) } MSP Accounts GraphQL Query, First Page
          %a.rounded.border.border-gray-200.p-3.font-medium.transition.hover:border-sky-500.hover:bg-sky-50.dark:border-gray-700.dark:hover:border-sky-400.dark:hover:bg-gray-800{ href: msp_graphql_query_path(kind: "full", msp_account_id: @msp_relationship.fetch(:msp_account_id), admin_user_id: @admin_user_id) } MSP Users and Groups GraphQL Query, First Page
        %a.rounded.border.border-gray-200.p-3.font-medium.transition.hover:border-sky-500.hover:bg-sky-50.dark:border-gray-700.dark:hover:border-sky-400.dark:hover:bg-gray-800{ href: "/graphiql" } GraphiQL
        %a.rounded.border.border-gray-200.p-3.font-medium.transition.hover:border-sky-500.hover:bg-sky-50.dark:border-gray-700.dark:hover:border-sky-400.dark:hover:bg-gray-800{ href: "http://localhost:11160/search?service=user-management-service" } Jaeger User Management Traces

    %section
      %h2.text-xl.font-semibold Account User Counts
      %p.mt-2.text-sm.text-gray-600.dark:text-gray-300
        - if @msp_relationship
          Showing the selected MSP-managed customer account. User count is loaded after private MSP discovery; normal account browsing is intentionally not exposed through the MSP mapping.
        - else
          Showing #{@display_account_ids.length} of #{@account_ids.length} accounts. User counts are computed for the full organization as #{@admin_user_id}.
      .mt-4.overflow-x-auto.rounded.border.border-gray-200.dark:border-gray-700
        %table.w-full.text-left.text-sm
          %thead.bg-gray-50.dark:bg-gray-800
            %tr
              %th.px-3.py-2 Account
              %th.px-3.py-2 Name
              %th.px-3.py-2 Parent
              %th.px-3.py-2 Users
              %th.px-3.py-2
          %tbody
            - @display_account_ids.each do |account_id|
              - account = @accounts_by_id[account_id]
              %tr.border-t.border-gray-200.dark:border-gray-700{ class: account_id == @selected_account_id ? 'bg-sky-50 dark:bg-gray-800' : nil }
                %td.px-3.py-2.font-mono.text-xs= account_id
                %td.px-3.py-2= account&.name || 'unloaded'
                %td.px-3.py-2.font-mono.text-xs= account&.parent_account_id.presence || '-'
                %td.px-3.py-2= @user_counts_by_account_id.fetch(account_id, 0)
                %td.px-3.py-2
                  - unless @msp_relationship
                    %a.font-medium.text-sky-700.hover:underline.dark:text-sky-300{ href: account_view_path(account_id, as: @admin_user_id) } Open
